New Records: Paul Stirling recorded his highest score of the season with 88 runs from 92 balls.
Key Match Events: Paul Stirling led the way with 88 from 92 balls.
Andy Balbirnie, Curtis Campher, Harry Tector, and Lorcan Tucker supported Stirling as Ireland posted 284-9.
Mark Adair took two wickets in a probing opening spell.
Craig Young and Graham Hume claimed three wickets each.
Spinner Matthew Humphreys bowled seven frugal overs, taking 1-16.
Jason Smith scored a fighting 91 for South Africa.
Post-Match Reflections: The question was asked if Ireland batting first would have made a difference, and the answer was an emphatic 'Yes'.
The series was lop-sided with the result in all three games effectively decided by the toss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ireland are likely to play another 'home series' in Abu Dhabi for commercial reasons.
